                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d736">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/1800: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-15T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 15, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:08 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>725. My 692, December 2, noon [<hi rend="italic">11 a.m.</hi>]. Today’s press
                    published the following communiqué from the official news agency EFE: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>By virtue of the law of November 23 which provides that the juridicial
                            regime of Tangier shall be subject to the laws for the Spanish
                            Protectorate in Morocco, the High Commissariat of Spain has assumed
                            charge of the services of police, finance, health, public works and, in
                            short, of all those services up to now dependent on the international
                            administration of Tangier which has thus been replaced in the form
                            foreseen.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Tangier.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Weddell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
